In Windows:
Graphviz http://www.graphviz.org/
    -install using .msi file

In Python 2.7:
Graphviz
	-install via “pip install graphviz”
PyGraphviz
    -download .whl file at http://www.lfd.uci.edu/~gohlke/pythonlibs/#pygraphviz
    -install via pip install

Try first ‘visualization_example’ in /Ryan/example.py. If receiving error: ValueError: Program neato not found in path,
Use Windows start to search for “Edit the System Environment Variables” and add in the “C:\Program Files (x86)\Graphviz2.38\bin” address to the variable “Path” in both the User variables and System variables.


